ables any remotes or wireless keypads.";i:18;s:12:"Aug 19 2008.";i:19;s:48:"My garage door will start to close then reverse.";i:20;s:41:"Then the opener light flashes on and off.";i:21;s:117:"Everything Ive read says this is because the safety sensors are misaligned blinded by direct sunlight or bad somehow.";i:22;s:52:"Well Ive checked the sensors and heres what I found.";i:23;s:116:"Most garage door openers have a lock button or a switch that will cause the garage door to stop and sometimes close.";i:24;s:133:"If youre not sure where the controls for this are or how to turn the lock feature on and off youll want to consult the owners manual.";i:25;s:33:"Check to see if your garage door.";i:26;s:100:"Heres my Craftsman Garage-Door Opener Model 13953985 Heres what its been doing the past three weeks.";i:27;s:174:"Stopping when closing numerous times lights blinking and etc when this happens - taking about 2-10 or more times of pressing either the car remote wireless outside remote or.";i:28;s:94:"The most common cause for your door not closing in the morning but will close at night is the.";i:29;s:68:"These sensors prevent the door from closing if the sensor beam gets.";i:30;s:83:"This safety feature is required on garage doors and keeps the door from closing on.";i:31;s:21:"Try the Wall Station.";i:32;s:102:"If these dont seem to resolve the issue you can move on to the wall station of the garage door opener.";i:33;s:111:"Here try to press and hold the interior wall station using constant pressure until the door touches the ground.";i:34;s:79:"If the door closes with this method then the issue lies with the safety sensor.";i:35;s:126:"When there is an issue with your safety sensors the opener will interpret this as an obstruction and refuse to close the door.";i:36;s:151:"If the issue is with the sensors youll likely find that you can use the garage door remote or wall-mounted switch to open the door but not to close it.";i:37;s:122:"In case of broken springs which your garage door heavily relies on for the operation the garage door opener couldnt close.";i:38;s:80:"One more reason for your garage door not closing properly is the damaged cables.";i:39;s:73:"Tracks comprise of one of the most important components of a garage door.";i:40;s:87:"Any damage of these tracks can simply make your garage door unable to close completely.";i:41;s:117:"If your garage door opens ok but wont close then its possible the safety reversing sensors are not correctly aligned.";i:42;s:67:"Dont just assume that if the path is clear that the sensors are ok.";i:43;s:42:"This problem bugged me for several months.";i:44;s:64:"Hopefully after you read this you wont have the same problem in.";}}